{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "name": "Yellow-breasted fruit dove", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-yellow-breasted-fruit-dove-63699df5", "name": "Yellow-breasted fruit dove", "englishName": "Yellow-breasted fruit dove", "latinName": "Ramphiculus occipitalis", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The yellow-breasted fruit dove (Ramphiculus occipitalis), known locally as balorinay, is a species of bird in the family Columbidae. It is endemic to the Philippines. Its natural habitat is tropical moist lowland forest. While it is listed as least concern in IUCN, it is declining due to habitat loss, hunting, and trapping for the illegal wildlife trade. This species was formerly placed in the genus Ptilinopus. It is illegal to hunt, capture, or keep yellow-breasted fruit-doves under Philippine Law RA 9147. Taxonomy The yellow-breasted fruit dove was formally described in 1844 by the English zoologist George Gray under the binomial name Ptilopus occipitalis. The type locality is the island of Luzon in the Philippines. The specific epithet occipitalis is from Latin, meaning \"of the back of the head\". The yellow-breasted fruit dove was formerly placed in the genus Ptilinopus. A molecular genetic study published in 2014 found that the fruit dove genus Ptilinopus was paraphyletic. In a move towards creating monophyletic genera, nine species including the yellow-breasted fruit dove were moved from Ptilinopus to Ramphiculus. Alternative names for the yellow-breasted fruit dove include sulphur-breasted fruit dove. Two subspecies are recognised. They are recognised only on the basis on minor differences in size and plumage, and may be better treated as monotypic. R. o. occipitalis (Gray, GR, 1844) – lowland forest of northern and central Philippines R. o. incognitus (Tweeddale, A, 1877) – mountains of Mindanao (southeastern Philippines) Description It is locally known as siete colores, which means 7 colors and has been nicknamed by birdwatchers as sapin-sapin, which is a multicolored Filipino desert. The yellow-breasted fruit dove is one of over 50 species in the genus Ptilinopus. Within the genus, it is most closely allied to the red-eared fruit dove and the Lompobattang fruit dove. Ecology and behavior It is a frugivore.The Philippine green pigeon usually occurs singly or in small groups with other doves to feed on fruiting trees. Its flight is fast and direct, with the regular beats and an occasional sharp flick of the wings that are characteristic of pigeons in general. Habitat and conservation status Its natural habitat is moist tropical primary lowland forest up to 1,800 meters above sea level. The IUCN has classified the species as being of least concern but the population is believed to be declining due to deforestation from land conversion, Illegal logging and slash-and-burn farming. This species also experiences hunting pressure for both meat and the pet trade. References Cited source Gibbs, David; Barnes, Eustace (2010). Pigeons and Doves: A Guide to Pigeons and Doves of the World. Christopher Helm. ISBN 978-1-4081-3555-6.", "shortSummary": "The yellow-breasted fruit dove (Ramphiculus occipitalis), known locally as balorinay, is a species of bird in the family Columbidae. It is…", "threats": ["栖息地破坏", "猎捕压力", "森林砍伐"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/YellowBreastedFruitDove2.jpg/960px-YellowBreastedFruitDove2.jpg", "order": "Columbiformes", "family": "Columbidae", "genus": "Ptilinopus", "species": "Ptilinopus occipitalis", "orderCn": "鸽形目", "familyCn": "鸠鸽科", "genusCn": "果鳩屬", "speciesCn": "Yellow-breasted fruit dove", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-ptilinopus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-ptilinopus", "species": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis"}, "expandable": true, "x": -947.12, "y": -2.68, "z": -55.43}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-ptilinopus", "name": "果鳩屬", "latinName": "Ptilinopus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "果鳩屬（Ptilinopus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联54种鸟类，如Scarlet-breasted fruit dove、Wompoo fruit dove、Yellow-breasted fruit dove等54种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 54, "x": -502.5, "y": -116.1, "z": -36.72}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "name": "Yellow-breasted fruit dove", "latinName": "Ptilinopus occipitalis", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Yellow-breasted fruit dove（Ptilinopus occipitalis）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Yellow-breasted fruit dove。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -947.12, "y": -2.68, "z": -61.02}], "links": [{"key": "bird-yellow-breasted-fruit-dove-63699df5__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "source": "bird-yellow-breasted-fruit-dove-63699df5", "target": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-ptilinopus", "source": "taxonomy-species-ptilinopus-occipitalis", "target": "taxonomy-genus-ptilinopus", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Yellow-breasted fruit dove 属于属 果鳩屬。"}]}
